Cook,<br><br>
This is a great post, one which many of us have been feeling for some time.  Thanks for putting our thoughts to words.<br><br>
You talked about our tactics, and to me it seemed that the North Vietnamese &quot;borrowed&quot; our tactics from the War of Independence, and we took on the role, or at least the fighting style, of the British in the 1700's.  <br><br>
Is is possible that when an Army gets so ingrained and political it cannot adapt its overall strategy to new circumstances?  We tried to overcome stratigic blunders with technology--that worked to keep us in the game (at a very great price), but ultimately we pulled out and basically gave the war to the Vietnamese.  <br><br>
Any thoughts along these lines?
